Data-sources

pandas-datareader is a Python library that provides up-to-date remote data access for pandas, making it easy to pull financial and economic data into a DataFrame.

Repository: https://github.com/pydata/pandas-datareader


Nasdaq Data Link is a data platform with both free and paid datasets: free includes open/public datasets and premium samples, while paid covers most of the full financial and alternative-data catalog. The official repo for the R package is here: https://github.com/nasdaq/data-link-r


